-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/germany-s-rwe-offers-japan-help-with-nuclear-plants-bild-says.html
German energy company  RWE AG (RWE)  has
offered  Japan  help in making its nuclear power plants secure
after the March 11 earthquake, Chief Executive Juergen Grossman
said today in an  interview  with Bild Zeitung. German power
plants are built to very high standards for protection against
earthquakes, he said in the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 